cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.SY

This paper proposes a novel architecture for hierarchical reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks, which are common applications of reinforcement learning. Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of the proposed architecture in credit assignment, which is a fundamental problem in control systems (cs.SY).
